    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>New York Nov 12. 1877.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. &#38; dear friend<lb/></p>
            <p>Never until<lb/> I was so fortunate as to<lb/> become a member of<lb/> your household could<lb/> I comprehend how in<lb/> such a short space<lb/> of time it were possi&#45;<lb/>ble for me to feel<lb/> so entirely <hi rend="underline">at home</hi><lb/> as I did within<lb/> your charmed circle<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>&#45;&#45;and to have occasion<lb/> to terminate it all so<lb/> suddenly&#44; and to pass<lb/> to a scene so terribly<lb/> melancholy&#44; has brought<lb/> with it regrets never<lb/> to be forgotten&#44; and<lb/> cast a pall upon<lb/> my thoughts not<lb/> soon to be removed.<lb/>  Accept my sincere<lb/> thanks for your&#44; and<lb/> your families kind<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>hospitality to me&#44; and<lb/> I trust some day<lb/> to have it in my<lb/> power to repay in<lb/> part your generosity.<lb/>  Best love to Nina&#44; I<lb/> hope she will write<lb/> to me soon.  I remain&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours affectionately<lb/>
            Ida J. Solomons.<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
